up 11th graf pvs: Police officials...</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By K.P. HONG</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A chartered fishing boat with 48 people aboard collided with a <LOCATION> Japanese </LOCATION> navy submarine and quickly sank Saturday near <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, leaving at least three people dead and 27 missing, police said. The 92-foot boat, chartered for a weekend fishing expedition, sank less than two minutes after the collision, said police in the nearby port city of <LOCATION> Yokosuka </LOCATION>. They said 19 people were rescued from the boat but a 38-year-old man died in a hospital. Divers subsequently recovered two bodies on Sunday, said a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Maritime </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s coast guard None of the 75 men aboard the diesel-powered submarine were reported injured, said officials with the <ORGANIZATION> Maritime </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Self-Defense </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>'s navy. Officials said Sunday that divers located the boat at a depth of more than 150 feet. Officials said about 80 divers and 40 boats were taking part in the search. The <ORGANIZATION> Maritime </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> spokesman said the cause of the accident was still under investigation and captains of both vessels had been called in for questioning. According to <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> television, the collision occurred after one of the vessels swerved to the right to avoid another boat. Television news reports showed the submarine floating on the surface near the accident site with no apparent damage. A handful of men on its deck and hull scanned the surrounding waters and life rafts were lined along its top. Police officials said the submarine, the 2,200-ton Nadashio, hit the fishing boat, the 15