<ORGANIZATION> Kyodo </ORGANIZATION> said. The mouth of <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION> is known for its congestion of military vessels, including <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> naval ships, ocean-going vessels, ferries, fishing boats and privately owned yachts and sightseeing boats. <LOCATION> Yokosuka </LOCATION> is the site of a major <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Naval base. The submarine, built by <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Heavy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION>, was commissioned in March 1984. It has two diesel engines and is equipped with six torpedo tubes.
