 have been threatened by changing agricultural practices. In response, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trust </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> for </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Historic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Preservation </ORGANIZATION> last year sponsored a contest on remodeling old barns for modern uses. <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Humstone </PERSON>, director of the Denver-based Barn Again program, said the 500 entries showed many economically feasible ways for farmers to continue using their barns rather than replacing them.
