<HEAD>Report Says Secret Talks Held On Southwestern Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Military officials from <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Cuba </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> met privately on an island off the African coast in an effort to work out a peace accord for southwestern <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, a news report said Sunday. The Portuguese news agency <ORGANIZATION> Lusa </ORGANIZATION> quoted a <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Verde </LOCATION> government spokesman as saying the meetings occurred last week on the island of <PERSON> Sal </PERSON> in the <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Verde </LOCATION> archipelago. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>'s foreign minister, <PERSON> Pik </PERSON> <PERSON> Botha </PERSON>, confirmed that representatives of the four nations met on the island Thursday and Friday. He did not name the representatives. `` During the meeting, there was an exchange of views on the military situation which will continue to be discussed in the forthcoming meeting to be held in <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION>,'' he said. After U.S.-mediated negotiations in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, the nations on July 20 announced an agreement in principle for the withdrawal of foreign troops from <LOCATION> Angola </LOCATION> and independence for neighboring <LOCATION> South-West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>, which is also known as <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION> has ruled <LOCATION> Namibia </LOCATION> for 73 years. More talks are scheduled in <LOCATION> Geneva </LOCATION> next month. The Portuguese agency quoted unidentified <LOCATION> Cape </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Verde </LOCATION> officials as saying that the talks there were mediated by <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> official <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Wood </PERSON>. It quoted the officials as saying the talks m