<HEAD>Government Balks at Paying Mortgage on Seized House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The federal government is refusing to pay off the mortgage on a confiscated $ 1.1 million home, arguing that <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> should have known the house was bought with drug money. `` At best for the bank, Republic stuck its head in the sand to avoid obtaining the knowledge of the drug connection,'' Assistant <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Dagen </PERSON> charged in court papers. Republic seeks repayment on its loan to a Panamanian company the government says was controlled by convicted smuggler <PERSON> Indalecio </PERSON> <PERSON> Iglesias </PERSON>. `` If this is upheld, it could force banks to run <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION> checks on every borrower,'' said <PERSON> Stan </PERSON> <PERSON> Beiley </PERSON>, attorney for Republic. Under federal laws, the government may seize properties bought or built with drug profits, or homes in which drug deals occurred. The laws also provide that the government must honor mortgages or liens on seized properties _ if the mortgage holder is an innocent party. After the government seized the palatial five-bedroom home in an exclusive <ORGANIZATION> Coral </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cables </ORGANIZATION> neighborhood last month, the bank asked that its one-year $ 800,000 mortgage be paid off when the house was sold. But the government refused. Federal prosecutors contend in court documents that <PERSON> Iglesias </PERSON> was laundering his ill-gotten gains when his <ORGANIZATION> Thule </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holding </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> pledged its sole asset _ the house _ as collateral for the mortgage in 1987. `` Of course, we did n't know anything about it. We had no idea,'' Republic President <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> la </PERSON> <PERSON> Mata </PERSON> told The <ORGANIZ